description:
This is the first episode of my experimental Harvest Moon 64 LP & WalkThrough.

This is a casual game that you can play at your own pace. Recently though I've learned the advanced mechanics of the game and the many requirements needed to finish the game with a perfect ending.

My goal is to finish the game with all 16 photos in the album and receive a perfect evaluation without intentionally using any game glitches, exploits, or "strategies" that I consider cheap. These include, but are not limited to:

#1: No use of gameshark codes.
#2: No taking advantage of affection exploits. (such as the Karen/dog exploit, multiple music boxes, animal abuse, etc.)
#3: No cheap tool leveling. I may only level up a tool by using it for its purpose and outside.
#4: No save state / replay abuse to get what I want, unless it's required or within reason.
#5: Along with rule #4, no intentional weather manipulation unless required. (ex. needing a sunny Fall 7th)
#6: I am only allowed to have 1 free drink a day. (no infinite stamina from wine, milk, water)
#7: I am not allowed to use the horse and dogs race glitch to get free medals.
#8: I am not allowed to use medical herbs if my player is totally fatigued to prevent sickness.

For an extra self-imposed challenge, I must:
#1: Go to sleep before the day ends (6 am).
#2: Wait until the 3rd year before I can get the awesome blue power berry, which has the ability to prevent fatigue / sickness.

In this run I plan to get:
#1: 4001+ combined affection points from the villagers
#2: all 5 girls fall in love with me
#3: sick 0 days.
#4: 4 cows, 4 sheep, 6 chickens
#5: 9000+ shipped crops
#6: 1000+ shipped eggs or milk
#7: 201+ fish
#8: all 6 house extentions
#9: all 35 recipes
#10: 100,000G+ ending cash
#11: 220+ player happiness
#12: all 10 power berries and the super special blue power berry in year 3
#13: 384+ planted grass squares

Shoutouts to SomeCrazyGuy, kirbyarm, & Sam Van Dam for contributing most to the reverse engineering of Harvest Moon 64 to figure out exactly what is required to beat it.
Check out this guide if you want to learn the game's inner workings: http://www.gamefaqs.com/n64/197528-harvest-moon-64/faqs/41454
